<div class="container-fluid">
  <div class="row">
  <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-6 px-md-0 sign-up-left py-6">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="col-sm-10 mx-auto">
        <h3 class="form-title text-left mb-5">Welcome to <svg class="signup-ost-kit-logo">
          <switch>
            <use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ost-kit-logo"></use>
          </switch>
        </svg> alpha!</h3>
        <div class="block mb-5">
          <img src="https://dxwfxs8b4lg24.cloudfront.net/ost-kit/images/signup-mint-tokens@2x.png" class="float-left mr-3" alt="" width="99" />
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-weight-normal">Mint Branded Tokens</h4>
            <p>You will mint your own Branded Tokens on OpenST test side blockchains, by staking OST⍺ on Ethereum testnet. OST⍺ is a test version of the OST cryptocurrency that tracks the public market value of OST. In alpha, your Branded Tokens are only tradable within your ecosystem. The staking of OST⍺ functions as a reserve, backing the value of your tokens.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="block">
          <img src="https://dxwfxs8b4lg24.cloudfront.net/ost-kit/images/signup-simulate-transactions@2x.png" class="float-left mr-3" alt="" width="99"/>
          <div>
            <h4 class="font-weight-normal">Simulate Transactions</h4>
            <p>You can setup various transaction types, add more users, and run simulations directly in OST KIT or via our developer APIs. Track and analyse your token economy in the dashboards. Audit transactions on the OpenST blockchain with the OST VIEW block explorer.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <hr class="my-4"/>
        <h4 class="form-title text-left mb-3">Important Notes</h4>
        <p class="important-notes p-2 m-0">
          OST KIT alpha operates in a test environment. Transactions are not real and the cryptocurrency that changes hands has no real value.
        </p>
        <p class="important-notes p-2 m-0">
          MetaMask is required to participate. You will use MetaMask on Ropsten Test Network to sign for token creation transactions.
        </p>
        <p class="important-notes p-2 m-0">
          There is no user-facing wallet in alpha. You will simulate transactions from the company perspective only.
        </p>
        <p class="important-notes p-2 m-0">
          You will get an initial allotment of OST⍺. You can request additional OST⍺ as needed.
        </p>
        <p class="important-notes p-2 m-0">
          You can use OST PRICER, our price oracle, to fix prices in USD for transactions in your community.
        </p>
        <p class="important-notes p-2 m-0">
          There are no price stabilisation features implemented in alpha. The value of your tokens will fluctuate with the market price of OST.
        </p>
        <p class="important-notes p-2 m-0">
          There is no cashing-out or exchanging of Branded Tokens in alpha. In the future, holders of your token will have a legal right to the staked OST backing your token, enabling them to cash out or exchange one Branded Token for another.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="col-sm-12 col-md-4 mx-auto py-6">
    <form id="sign_up_form" class="user-form"
          action="/api/client/sign-up" method="POST"
          data-ost-formhelper data-redirect="/planner"
    >

      <h3 class="text-left">Register for <svg class="signup-ost-kit-logo">
        <switch>
          <use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#ost-kit-logo"></use>
        </switch>
      </svg> alpha</h3>
      <div class="general_error invalid-feedback" data-forid="sign_up_form">&nbsp;</div>

      <div class="row">
        <div class="col">
          <div class="form-group mb-2" id="tokenNameFormGrp">
            <label class="form-label" data-forid="token_name">Token Name</label>

            <input id="user-token-name" type="text" name="token_name" class="form-control" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder="Enter token name" required/>
            <div class="invalid-feedback" data-forid="token_name">&nbps;</div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col">
          <div class="form-group m-0" id="emailFormGrp">
            <label class="form-label" data-forid="email">Token Symbol</label>

            <input id="user-token-symbol" type="text" pattern="\w{3,4}" name="token_symbol" class="form-control" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder="Enter token symbol" required  maxlength="4" />
            <div class="invalid-feedback" data-forid="token_symbol">&nbps;</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="text-center form-group">
        <label class="form-label d-block text-left mb-2" data-forid="email">Select icon for your token</label>
        <ul class="radio-group list-unstyled text-center">
          <li>
            <input type="radio" id="option-one" name="token_icon" value="token_icon_1" checked>
            <label for="option-one" class="mb-0">
              <span class="token_icon token_icon_1"></span>
            </label>
          </li>
          <li>
            <input type="radio" id="option-two" name="token_icon" value="token_icon_2">
            <label for="option-two" class="mb-0">
              <span class="token_icon token_icon_2"></span>
            </label>
          </li>
          <li>
            <input type="radio" id="option-three" name="token_icon" value="token_icon_3">
            <label for="option-three" class="mb-0">
              <span class="token_icon token_icon_3"></span>
            </label>
          </li>
          <li>
            <input type="radio" id="option-four" name="token_icon" value="token_icon_4">
            <label for="option-four" class="mb-0">
              <span class="token_icon token_icon_4"></span>
            </label>
          </li>
          <li>
            <input type="radio" id="option-five" name="token_icon" value="token_icon_5">
            <label for="option-five" class="mb-0">
              <span class="token_icon token_icon_5"></span>
            </label>
          </li>
          <li>
            <input type="radio" id="option-six" name="token_icon" value="token_icon_6">
            <label for="option-six" class="mb-0">
              <span class="token_icon token_icon_6"></span>
            </label>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="form-group mb-2" id="emailFormGrp">
        <label class="form-label" data-forid="email">Email address</label>

        <input id="user-email" type="email" name="email" class="form-control" aria-describedby="emailHelp" placeholder="Enter email" required/>
        <div class="invalid-feedback" data-forid="email">&nbps;</div>
      </div>

      <div class="form-group mb-0">
        <div class="clearfix">
          <label class="form-label float-left" for="password">Password</label>
          <span class="form-label float-right text-capitalize font-weight-light" style="color: #6c9ba9">Min 8 characters</span>
        </div>
        <div class="input-group mb-2">
          <input type="password" class="form-control form-control-input-group" placeholder="Password"
                 id="password" name="password" required minlength="8" />
          <div class="input-group-append">
        <span class="input-group-text input-group-inline input-group-eye">
          <svg class="icon">
            <switch>
              <use xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xlink:href="#icon-eye"></use>
            </switch>
          </svg>
        </span>
          </div>
          <div class="invalid-feedback" data-forid="password">&nbps;</div>
        </div>
        <!-- ZXCVBN Wrap -->
        <div class="zxcvbn-group mb-3"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="form-group has-error mb-2" id="tosFormGrp">
        <div class="form-check p-0">
          <input id="tos" class="checkbox-custom form-check-input" name="agreed_terms_of_service" type="checkbox" required>
          <label for="tos" class="checkbox-custom-label form-check-label">
            <span class="tos-text">By checking this box, you agree to our <a href="" class="font-weight-normal">Terms of Service</a> &amp; acknowledge and consent to our <a href="" class="font-weight-normal">Privacy Policy</a>.</span>
          </label>
          <div class="invalid-feedback" data-forid="agreed_terms_of_service">&nbps;</div>
        </div>

      </div>

      <div class="form-group text-center" >
        <button type="submit" class="btn btn-gold" data-submiting="Registering">Register</button>
        <small class="form-text text-muted" style="line-height: 40px">Have an account already?</small>
        <a href="/login" class="btn ost-btn-secondary" title="Login">Login</a>
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
  </div>
</div>



